Can&#039;t find any follow-ons to this entry. Am I missing them, or are they still in progress? Thanks for the great post - we&#039;re migrating to Win7 and this is exactly the kind of info I&#039;m looking for!

The cost is a tricky one. The total hardware cost is spread across multiple years, as I started with my latest gaming system which in turn started with an existing monitor, case, and power supply.&lt;br /&gt;
The motherboard, CPU, memory, and hard drives total to something in the $1200 range. The case and PSU are probably in the $250 range. Graphics card was pretty expensive when I purchased it and still above $200, but you don&#039;t really need anything too powerful for a virtual lab.&lt;br /&gt;
One thing I considered doing was upgrading the power supply to a more powerful unit and buying an SSD (or 2) to install my primary OS on, but I can&#039;t complain - even with one mismatched SATA 1 drive (that&#039;s a whole different story) in my RAID 10 volume I&#039;m getting a 5.9 for windows experience (5.9 on storage, 7.4+ on everything else).&lt;br /&gt;
